Agreed on keyword args. I maintain Requests for PHP [1] which has a very similar API to Python Requests, and at the moment, you have to use an array as the options parameter.<p><pre><code>    $options = ['timeout' => 0.5];
    $r = Requests::get('https://api.github.com/', $headers, $data, $options);
</code></pre>
[1]: <a href="http://requests.ryanmccue.info/" rel="nofollow">http://requests.ryanmccue.info/</a>
